caption: Miss you so much! A favorite haunt. Hope you’re able to reopen soon!
Lovely dive bar, can't wait for it to reopen.
Great German beer
Always a favorite when I come back to DC! Great beer and a hot pot of mussels.
Mussels great

St. Arnold's offers delicious mussels and a large Belgian beer selection. The prices are fair but I'd recommend going during happy hour for an even better deal. The service is good but can occasionally be a bit inattentive when it's busy. The bartenders are great.
Great beer selection, service and Flemish stew! One of my favorite places to eat in DC!
Delicious PEI mussels!

This was one of the most memorable late night dinners we had on our DC trip.  It was within walking distance of the Mayflower, where we stayed before Christmas.  After making a visit to Washington Monument and making our way down to the Lincoln Memorial, we worked up an appetite.  We love that this dive bar was open late.  The food was SO GOOD!  And, the service was even better.  The bartender we had made our night.  Saying she was phenomenal would be an understatement.  Unfortunately, I'm terrible with names, otherwise she'd get the shutout she deserves.  St. Arnold's is truly an awesome Belgian restaurant.  I'm not going to hesitate to recommend the Thai Curry mussels and frites, if you like spicy, bold flavors.  It was perfection on a cold night.  We used all the bread we had to sop up that juice.  It was probably the best set of moules-frites I've ever had.  In addition to washing it down with their selection on tap, we also shared the liege waffle, which was just standard fare.
Paul is an amazing bartender!
The muscles are always amazing! The bar crew is my favorite because they can always suggest a great beer! Nothing better than a bartender who wants to share their love of beer!
Great mussel bar with great beer choices! Loved their happy hour options.
Good beer list, decent service. Cool basement level digs.
My favorite spot in DC. How can you go wrong with duck fat mussels and Belgium beer??
Friendly atmosphere, European beers, apparently a Texans bar but not by their choice.
Great selection of mussels. Great food and service. Tucked away off the beaten path so clientele tends to be regulars.
Good atmosphere, wait staff very nice!  Was there for lunch.. Many issues with the kitchen getting orders correct, food was ok..
The best mussels I’ve ever had hands down. Complemented by some of the best fries, bread, dipping sauce, and legit Belgian beer. 🤤🤤 fantastic
It was a great place for cocktails with the guys. Really good Old Fashioned.
Great beers and food and service and an especially cozy atmosphere

Every time I come to DC, I have to go here. They have 20 different types of sauce. You can order it by the pound. Usually I go with my spouse, and will order two different kinds and share them both. Get extra bread.
Best frites period. Wonderful service fun and homeu

Great selection of mussels! No shortage of options for beer and mussels, this used to be our go-to happy hour spot. They recently increased their happy hour prices which has caused our group to start going elsewhere. The food is good quality and the ambience is small-pub style, although seating can be limited during peak hours, so you might need a reservation if you have a group. Friendly, quick service. If they kept their previous happy hour prices we would have kept this our weekly meeting spot.
very welcoming staff and hence great atmosphere.  nice selection of beers.  food is good!
Great good,  great entertainment
Food is really good,  but beware if you order a mixer from the bar,  ours wasn't even close
Great Belgian restaurant with excellent Belgian beer selection and a wide variety of mussles
Love the mussels here! Happy hour is the best. Had almost every type of mussels dish here and haven't had a bad one yet. Tables are super close together, but food is delicious
Nice hole in the wall place. Good atmosphere & good beer! I was never to fond of mussels but this place made me change my mind! Peter at the bar has great customer service. Will definitely be back.
Delicious mussels and I'm not even a fan of mussels. I've come twice so far and already planning our next visit. Friendly staff and nice little tavern ambience.
Classy, understated, delicious food and most importantly great service!
Lovely place and delicious mussels/beer

Mussel heaven. So many ways to have mussels done, only got to sample 2 styles but damnit they were great. The beer is also a perfect compliment. If this small place is packed, wait. It is well worth it.

Tons of selection on the menu for mussels.  I had the "house" mussels which were very good.  The fries were also well cooked and come with all the mussel dishes.  Large selection of primarily Belgian beers, which typically aren't my favorite but I found a sour I really enjoyed.  Small cozy atmosphere, and good service.
Loved this place!  Best mussells and the service was great!
Homiest spot in dupont

Love the mussels and fries. Hard to decide which type of mussels dish to order they all look so good. I had one of the traditional options on my last visit. Only issue I have is that some of the beers are really expensive.
Very good
Great comfort food!

Excellent place. Located in oldish brick basement, it serves wide variety of Belgian beer and cooked mussels. For those, who thinks that beer was invented in US (and not in Egypt as it was), they have some options too. They also have non-seafood options, if you have allergy, but it's not their specialty. House mussels are extremely tasty, paired with good Belgian wheat unfiltered - exceptional. IMHO, fries are just a distraction here - just ask for more bread instead. Staff is very friendly, professional and nice! Music selection is very good (it was when I was there!) All in all, perfect place if you have an hour or two to kill.
Always a pleasure. I can rely on the mussels and frittes being hot and delicious. Lots of other options as well.
Great steak and cheese special on wednesdays!
Best mussels in town!!!
Wonderful staff !
Happy hour mussels and beers here are the best. The place WILL get crowded so your best bet is to get there before 5:30 otherwise your group may not get a table. My go-to order is the truffle one :-)
So good, don't miss
Happy hour mussels were amazing. Good atmosphere.
Food is incredible
Great beer selection,  you can get .3L, .5L and 1L. Food was fantastic

Great place for mussels and beer.  They do mussels all sorts of different ways and they do it well.  They have some really good beers too, but theselection could be bigger.  The selection is good, but when it comes to Belgian beer there is a lot of great ones out there.  The low point was that the frites were only good not great.  The service was perfect too.  I always have a great time here.
Great atmosphere and service! I bowl of mussles is enough for two people since it comes with a generous side of fries. Great place to try.
Excellent Service...
Excellent bartender. Treated us like Family ❤️

This place is AHHHHMAZING! Im speaking of the food.  Had waffles, chicken,  wings, cheese board & fries. Sooooo good.  2 thumbs up.  We also loved how laid back the atmosphere was. Dim lighting & good 80'sish music. Very awesome  service! Visiting from Tampa, would absolutely come back for food.
Delicious!

A bit dimly lit and noisy for a lunch crowd. Mussels were solid while service was a little unpolished. Would go back for happy hour, but not for lunch or dinner. A good spot to start of your night with a quick beer ... But there is just something not so great about being subterranean
This place is amazing , their menu is outstanding. The flavors are so unique and delicious.
Love love love the mussels and the beer selection is great!
The best mussels, fries, and selection of Belgian beers. Go during happy hour (M-F, 3:30 pm-6:30 pm) when you can get any variety of mussels for $11 and $6 half-liters of some beer.
Good mussels.
Great mussels and beer selection
Best mussels bar in DC!
Great beer, food and staff
Great beer and atmosphere. Little pricey, but good for an occasional drink.

I have tried many of the menu items and everything tasted great. The service is always awesome. Everything is cooked to perfection. I have introduced this place to my friends and everyone loves it. In addition to the variety of mussels you can find something that you would like here.

Two dozen kinds of mussels and excellent fries!  Downside would be the Belgian waffles at the end.  Six bucks and was no better at all then one made at home.  Was hoping for better.  Their onion rings were also disgusting with almost no flavor or seasoning so I’d stay away from those too.  However their beer specials and choices were great and those mussels were very very good!  Just wasn’t happy with the waffles and onion rings but the beer and mussels were amazing!

Great restaurant and bar. They have a great selection of beers and food. The service was very good and it's a very cozy place. Would definitely go back and recommend it to someone who hasn't been before.  If you're looking to make reservations though they require you to have 4 or more people.

Great little bar. The owner was tending bar and super friendly and engaging in conversation. We did happen to be there on open mic night for striving comedians which was interesting to say the least....
Great beer and mussels. Non pretentious place to relax
Best mussels in town

As a Belgian-American, maybe my favorite stop for Belgian food and drink in DC. Excellent moules frites and a great beer list. Friendly staff, a cozy atmosphere, situated in a great location for a dinner after work. Highly recommended -- very authentic!
Loved the comedy club!!
Great beer and mussels!
Mussels and Fries. Done right. So good I ordered a second pot.
Love the relaxed ambience and the food was great!

Mussels like you'd get in Belgium.  A wide selection of preparations for this signature food with an impressive tap list to ensure you'll find just the right Belgian beer to go along with your meal.  This time I had the Flemish Onion Soup and Beef Carbonade.  The soup was flavorful with a generous cheese topping, the beef was fall-apart tender in a rich, deep, delicious gravy and the fries were crisp - excellent across the board.
Solid mussel spot off the beaten path on Jefferson in Dupont. Def worth a visit.
Great beer selection! Delirium! And the mussels and fries are amazing too.

The best mussels I've ever had!  I came here on a double date with my girlfriend, best friend, and his girlfriend.  We had an amazing time.  The beer selection is great and has a lot of variety!  We ordered the mussels and onion rings for apps which were both delicious, and then we got the burgers for dinner which were incredible.  One of the best meals I've had in a while.  The service was pretty good as well, considering they only had one waitress working that Monday night.  I can't wait to come back here!

Horrible experience I’ve never had from any other places. I would give a minus if I can. We came in 2 groups of 4 and 2 and asked to moved the table of 2 to sit next to each other and they strongly refused. The waitress kept saying “Nope.” “No.” And when we asked if we can all move to another available space she said “It’s over.”  They claimed they had a reservation for 8 and planed to move that available table to the next one which is occupied by another party all along. We’re there until late but that reservation they mentioned never happen. The table we asked to move to still available until we left.  I don’t understand why wouldn’t a restaurant accommodate their customer when they obviously can. We bought their promotion voucher and that shouldn’t be the case. A voucher should attract and impress customer so they would come again. Not to be treated like this.  Once and never again. Better food and service elsewhere.
Quite and excellent service !!
Food is great but the atmosphere is a bit dark.
Wonderful place.  Great food and beer
Good mussels and beer. Neat atmosphere

Cozy little Belgian beer spot with a great menu and a chilled out tavern vibe.  They are known for their mussels but as I'm not a mussels guy I can't speak to them.  Definitely recommend this place for lunch, happy hour is a bite of dinner.

Amazing mussels as always! Not to mention perfectly crisped frites & crusty bread ! Met a client here for lunch..impressed as well. You can't go wrong at St. Arnold's. Keep up the good work Peter & Kelly!

I've only had one experience here, but considering there's another St. Arnold's I frequent, this one doesn't quite stack up. Servers not as attentive especially during happy hour as the other one. Food was a bit sub par for St. Arnold's.

I had mussels. They were very good. I will go back. ST. Arnold's Dupont Circle has an extensive mussels menu! None like I have ever seen before. They cook to perfection. The staff is friendly. I will go back!
Great
Omg the mussels!  Really great spot. Amazing food and solid beer selection. Can't wait to go back!
Perfect little basement Belgian dive with primo mussels!

Classic location in DC. Mussels are superb, nice variety of beer on tap, and great service. It can get crowded as the space is small, but that's a credit to the popularity among locals. Other food is very good, with anything labeled as Belgian typically even better. DC has lost a number of pubs in this style, unfortunately. Let's all hope St Arnold's keeps going strong!  They clearly put in the work and maintain quality. I can't wait to head back.
St. Arnold’s is our favorite spot in this area of DC. We always sit at the bar and everyone is so friendly and welcoming. The food is delicious and the drafts are great.
I stumbled across this place before going to a comedy show. The mussels were amazing. The five star rating could be because I was pleasantly surprised, but I will be going back.
Get the mussels.  Great beer selection. Cozy place. A little loud at times
Great Belgian beer and food selections. Cozy atmosphere.
happy hour mussels special can't be beat
Good Belgian beer.
Always amazing!!
We had a group of 29 people for a company team event and we had a great time, the staff was amazing and never got overwhelmed.

As soon as I walked in I was greeted with hospitality. Further more, for no reason I was told ( or asked) I was given a FREE shot of whiskey. Then I ordered my drink. The wonderful person ( Larain, Spelling) kept up a fantastic conversation and made an outsider like me feel as welcome as a local.  I'm giving this place 5/5, good food and drink selection and marvelous staff. Thank you for being one place in DC that I can sit down and have a nice relaxing drink with good conversation.
This was the best thing i put in my mouth in years. Had the mussels and omg still thinking about it now. Made me feel some kinda way. Wow. Good job.
Just try the mussels. You won't regret it. Bartender was very helpful picking out a winner since they have a lot of options. Beer selection is fantastic as well.
Great mussels, friendly staff.

A restaurant serving mussels in perhaps 15 unique preparations.  Enjoyed our first visit two years ago, so we went back on our next visit to the DC area. Good choices of beers, many from Belgium. Reasonable, especially if you get there during happy hour. Try it, you'll be pleasantly surprised.
Excellent food, quick service, friendly staff. Very pleased!!

One of the best food places I've had ever. Everyone is so nice there and well organized, everybody cares about you and is great. The food comes in like 5 mins and it is so good everything on the menu is good. I totally recommend it to anyone, it is so good

Nice place, completely devoid of flavor. I got the special, which was a bowl of plain noodles, a few pieces of spinach, some mussels, and the water they were apparently boiled in, which left me wondering whether the cook was simply confused and perhaps forgot to drain the water or add any flavor at all whatsoever. They also gave me a few slices of plain, stale white bread without so much as a pad of butter to join me in my quest. The bartender seemed like he was almost waiting for me to tap out and ask for some hot sauce in a desperate last-ditch attempt to taste anything at all. I’ve seen prison food that was more exciting than this.

Minus one star for service from one specific employee who clearly was going thru and took it out on the table. Shout out to the other waitress Tawana (sp?) who was super pleasant. Hope she got the tip. 💁🏾‍♀️ Mussels are definitely worth the visit. Causal place where you are not rushed and the food and flavors are solid. Enjoy!
Mussels and french fries - I never knew how much I needed this combo until now 😍
Great atmosphere, great place to hang out with friends.
Amazing food, great beer selection! If you're into mussels, this spot is a must!
best hideaway place and excellent muscles
Nice small Belgian joint with a wide variety of mussels dishes.  Beer list is very good as well.

I love this place for happy hour. Great specials on beer and food. Very unpredictable how busy they're going to be; I've had experiences where I'm one of the few people there and also times it's totally packed. Definitely worth the trip for a liter of Palm and some classic mussels.
Good food, great beer.
If you want to pound liters of dunkel and eat mussels, this is a solid place to checkout. They have an insane variety of mussel flavors.

A dive bar right outside Dupont that does mussels and frites the right way - Belgian style. And how could there be anything Belgian without the beer. Rotating European taps keep things interesting and have DC workers flocking here for happy hour. The happy hour, 4 til 630, offers buckets of their decadent and plump mussels for only $11 ($20 regularly). One can add fries too for only $15. The mussel broth selections are unparalleled to anywhere else in the city. To get anything better you would have to fly across the Atlantic. The cozy and dim cellar-like dining room makes it even more Euro. Go for the happy hour, you'll be happy you did.
Small place , but food is great.  Try to hit happy hour time !!

This is a hidden neighborhood gem. From the street it looked closed but once you walk in, it's a very lively place where you can have a tasty lunch and catch a sports game. The actual mussles were nice and meaty and the service was prompt and friendly. For my order, I added shrimp. For the $5 upgrade, I literally had 5 pieces of meduim-sized shrimp. But overall, I was well-pleased with the mussels and the variety on the menu.
Delicious mussles!
A fantastic establishment with delicious food and efficient service.
There are two places worth getting mussels in the city, and this is the better of the two. Many many mussels options, and liter beers galore.

(Translated by Google) The atmosphere is excellent, the best beers and not to mention the menu. It is attended by the owner, so the service is superb. Family and night place to go with friends.  (Original) El ambiente es excelente, las mejores cervezas y ni se diga de la carta.  Lo atiende el dueño, así que el servicio es magnífico.  Lugar familiar y de noche para ir con amigos.
Good mussels
Good food, beer and service
Amazing mussels, nice atmosphere and delicious beer!  You have to get mussels in duck fat sauce!  And save whatever you can for dipping

caption: Mussels are OK. Gets extremely noisy.
Cozy place for great mussels. Hard to beat the classic St Arnold's pot.
A definite must when in DC.  Well prepared mussels.  Delicious!  Quaint.  Great service.
(Translated by Google) It's a bit expensive, is not it.  (Original) ちょっと高いかな。
Very good mussels, solid Belgian beer selection
Great food and drink. Great atmosphere!
Great for Business Dinner.
Food good...VERY noisy
Very good service and I love the mussels here! Excellent selection of beer and drinks

Love this place. Great mussels , good beer! It's small so I'd recommend calling ahead just to be safe. We had a birthday party here for a group of 18 and they accommodated us perfectly. It was a great night.
Dive bar with great food, good German beers
This place is great. Good beer, good food, great atmosphere.
Grear vibes, neighborhood bar.

This is a great spot -- especially if you are able to get there for happy hour. The prices during happy hour are great, when it's $11 for a big vat of mussels, but spike up to $20 when happy hour ends. There's also a great selection of beers here!
Ok salad, average service
I have never been there.... Sorry
Mussels and frites like Antwerp
Numerous craft beers and all kinds of mussels! What is there not to like!  The place is small so plan ahead, it is usually very crowded.
A new spot in my repertoire.  I'll definitely return for the savory mussels.
Amazing food and beer selection a bit hidden but a great spot to drink a beer and enjoy some delicious seafood.
A special place if you have a hankering for mussels.

Love this place. Perfect dive bar atmosphere with exceptional food. Always get mussels in some sort of beer and duck fat combo with fries. They are to die for. Also, they always taste fresh, not fishy. Our favorite lunch/dinner place in DuPont so far.
Won't separate the bill. Even after we explained that we are on a work trip and need separate itemized receipts. Food is ok. Beer is good. /Shrug
Really good mussels and beer menu eh. From Toronto and staff was really nice eh.
Good selection of Belgian beers on tap.

I was there two times this week. The first was on monday when I had a great time with my friend and stayed for a good 3 hours. Amazing beers and very good vibe. I liked it so much that I decided to invite my co-workers there on Thursday.  It was terrible... we were barely greeted, our waitress was rude and didn't make any effort to make us feel welcome. So much that we ended up leaving without even ordering. I was embarrassed but also surprised. It may be that she was having a bad day, or that our party was too colorful this time.  Unfortunately, her delivery was subject to interpretation and now I will never know.
A great place to get a liter of beer and some great mussels.  Definitely cozy and traditional bar atmosphere.   Would go again.
Great happy hour!
Great selection of mussels and beer. The wait staff gets the job done and are nice. I personally go every 2 months to meet up with friends. Great place.
Best mussel in DC. Very consistent food. Also, great happy hour.

Very authentic Belgian bar. I learned that although the owners aren't Belgian, they travel there every year just to keep up with the current trends in food and drinks. The beer selection is limited (compared to Belgium of course) but has some very nice options for Belgian beets on tap. As for the food, we only had some appetizers but they were excellent.  Flemish onion soup is flavourful and perfectly done and rye bread sticks are delicious!

The customer service was extremely friendly and efficient. The place is clean and the atmosphere is nice. But, the real reson to come here is for the decadent mussels, they are out of this world! The waffles are also quite delicious! Will definitely be coming back!
Food was good, price was fair, was a bit cramped, but I may have just been a busy night...though that's one of those good problems I guess.
Best place in the city for mussels
good!!
Awesome Flemish food, excellent beer selection and happy hour specials.
Great little hole in the wall with awesome mussels and good beer
I love mussels! This place has a menu of nothing but mussels! Yup, that's like heaven on earth baby!
Amazing happy hours
Great beer and food options. It gets a bit crowded during dinner time, so plan around a wait if you're looking to grab a bite at 8pm on a Friday!
Absolutely delicious. Their signature mussels were an absolute treat when paired with .5L pilsner. I highly recommend this place.
Not the best late night option. Lots of reviews that the food earlier in the night is really good. Later night you can get good from elsewhere and eat there.
Mussels and beer. Both excellent
Very good mussels in a cool underground location with good beers. All at a reasonable price-point. Definitely worth checking out.
Great beer, so many delicious mussel flavors. Great spot
Some of the best mussels in the DC area, for my taste. Good for a large group, if you can reserve ahead.

Small, no-thrills basement bar with a few TVs playing sports, and damn if isn't a great place to get mussels. Go for happy hour and grab a large pot of mussels (I recommend the house style) for $11 and add fries for $3 -- grab a .5l of three types of beer for $5 more and you can't beat it. Non-happy hour prices get a little more pricy, but still aint bad for DC.  Either way, if you've got a craving for mussels, fries, and other hideous (but delicious!) bar food, and large servings of European beer, you should definitely try St. Arnolds.

3.0 star rating 4/6/2017 1 check-in Would you pay 7 bucks for overly salted toasted bread stick that adds up to a single slice of bread? Yes? Then look no further.  I was ready to go on a mussel binge before I left the city. I looked up what's a good spot for some mussels and this popped up. I came in here, exhausted after a long walk around all the memorials, and I stood at the door for 5-10mins before anyone came up to seat me. There were only 1 other customer there at the time, not quite sure why it took so long for anyone to come seat me. Service aside, food is my main concern.  I started with the bread stick which was over salted and I downed two glasses of water while eating it. I came here for mussels and the duck fat stated as a cooking ingredient has got my full attention. I order the St. Arnold's signature mussels with added shrimp($5 for like 4-5 of them). The order came with fries and some bread for dipping. I'm not sure if it's the over salty starter ruining my tastebuds or if the mussel dish was not flavorful enough. I was pretty disappointed. Give me another chance and I would likely look for another spot to silence my craving.  Pro(s): - no wait?  Con(s): - Costly - Need work on balancing the flavors of the dishes
Good muscles

Great Belgian Mussel bar hidden in plain sight. Great decor and ambiance. Authentic Belgian and German beers, met bar owner, hilarious! Got a free whiskey chaser. Highly recommended but be warned: Beer is not cheap!!

(Translated by Google) First the bad: if they have "assiduous" beers (as happened to me with the Bavik) is that there is a lack of cleaning of the tube or the handles or that it is not stored under the conditions that it should. Then the good: mussels, with a beer sauce and duck fat with herbs, are dead. The second compensates the first.  (Original) Primero lo malo: si tienen cervezas "asidradas" (como a mi me pasó con la Bavik) es que falta limpieza del tubo o de los tiradores o que no se almacena con las condiciones que debiese. Después lo bueno: los mejillones, con una salsa de cerveza y grasa de pato con hierbas, están de muerte. Lo segundo compensa lo primero.
Best Mussels in DC, the kind you eat
Mostly have been here for drinks. Pretty good Belgian selection with a neighborhood bar feel. I hear the mussels are great and are half off during happy hour
Unbelievable how good this place is.  Great beer, sauces, and food is on point.
Amazing Muscles and beer selection
Best mussels in DC, 15+ different sauces. Fantastic fries,  great Belgian beers. Excellent service.
Cool spot.  Good food, great beer
Amazingly St. Arnolds might have the best buffalo wings in D.C. Their weekday happy hour prices are fantastic.

St. Arnold's is a true gem in DC, and that goes for both locations. The mussels are excellent, and while $20 is a lot - their $10 happy-hour special is well worth the effort to get to. I highly recommend their house specialty that they call "Mussels St. Arnold."
Great food. Great service.
Best mussels and a wide range of beer selection.
The best food I ever had. The mussels are amazing!
Big fan of the mussels. Liters of beer here.
Amazing! Great atmosphere..food and beer were great! Must go!

Their happy hour is great with the deals on beer and mussels. Such a great selection of each for all sorts of tastes. It's nice and cozy and though it seems loud it's pretty easy to carry on a conversation even when it's crowded.
Delicious mussels and fries. The spicy Italian was really good along with any of the classics.

This place is good fun. You basically get a large beer and if you want to eat, you get a bucket of steam mussels in various flavors with some fries and bread.The atmosphere is bar link. You can't go wrong with any of the flavors of mussels, but I particularly like the blue cheese flavor. It can be very loud in here during peak hours.
Great service, beer and mussels, in that order.
Delicious mussels and beer
Great mussels and beer selection.  Try the Thai curry mussels.  Happy hour is from 4-6:30 during the week and is well worth it
Always great mussels.  Really like the St. Arnolds special.  This place is one of the things I miss about living in DC.
My favorite spot when visiting DC!  Excellent mussels and beer. Don't add chicken to the mussels... Get overdone... Go with the sausage.
Great mussels
Belgians on draft. Mussels. Great service. What's not to love? 🍺
So good. As an out-of-town'r I sometimes worry about taking a chance.  This was an amazing atmosphere, great food, and excellent service!
Nice little basement bar/restaurant. Decent selection of Belgians on tap, but they need to rotate taps more.

great little spot if Mussels are your thing. My entree was delicious and my date was quiet and smiling as the mussels slowly disappeared out of the pot. I think I expected the bacon to be bite size & crispy as opposed to several entire strips of bacon (don't get me wrong, I LOVE bacon). I didn't mind the light level, gave it a slightly more intimate feel. Will be returning soon 😊
Fantastic Belgian bar with an ample selection of beers and a great atmosphere.  Also, oddly enough, the best burger in DC (yes, in my opinion, better than Duke's).

This place is amazing.  Mussels good.  It's a good place to take a first date if you're trying to be shady as hell, because it's hella dark inside.  I will say that the waitress this time around needs to chill out.  She barely gave us time to go through the menu.  We got the menu, and like 2 minute later, she was asking for drink orders.  When we said we needed more time, she agreed, and back like literally 2 minutes later.  And she continued to do this for all of the party members, and then once we had our food, she straight up disappeared, and then the service took a turn for the worst.  There was none.
This charming basement bar had a wonderful selection of beers and delicious fries
Great place
Good
Dark, rustic, pub-like atmosphere. Bartenders are very nice. Good beer selection and large portions. MUCH RECOMMEND!

Great neighbor bar atmosphere, with very friendly bartenders and servers. The place is fairly small and dimly lit, but felt comfortable. Fair selection of Belgian, German and specialty beers (not a huge selection though), and a good bar food menu. Mussels (I have the 3 philosophers version) with seasoned fries were solid. Highly recommend St. Arnold's for a casual meal or relaxed beer stop near DuPont Circle.
Any of the mussels were absolutely amazing. Great Belgian beers available as well!
Food was meh and decent beer selection. Got the chicken sandwich and the chicken had no flavor or was spiced correctly.
Always good... I normally do the St Arnold's mussels with fries and extra bread. Oh and don't touch the pots.

Had some of the best wings I've ever eaten right here. Extra crispy, habenero sauce & a side of bbq. Yum! Great selection of really good beers and excellent service. My first time here was a Tuesday and I went back for more wings that Friday!
Delicious mussels, solid HH prices. It's hard to go wrong here!

Great beer selection, wonderful food, bartender was a true bartender and an interesting group for a Monday night. Definitely a place I'm going to be stopping by again with colleagues and friends. Could be a standard go to if I were living here.

Just awesome. The food is very good and the beer is actually the best beer I ever had in America. Fresh german tab beer and also local American beer. The people you meet here are incredible friendly and the owner is a nice guy as well. I totally recommend it!!!
Good place
Best mussels in DC. Great beer selection and amazing happy hour mussels and beer specials.
I had the Italian mussels and they were fantastic. The service was friendly and very attentive. Will definitely come back again soon.
Get the Arnold's specialty mussels.  Good fries, great broth for dipping.  Very loud when busy which is often.  Very friendly & efficient bar service.
Excellent and tasty. Happy hours are a great deal.
Fun place.  Great Belgian beers and nice selection of tasty mussels.

I used to LOVE this place.  Seemed like a nice out of the way bar close to the busy DuPont Circle area.  Friendly bar tenders - good atmosphere - average food.  Sadly that all changes Saturday night - around 10:30pm my friend and I took a detour from Dupont Circle to duck into Arnold's for a drink.  Not real crowded - a few open tables and some open seats at the bar.  We were greeted by a hostess - who was a hostess in name only.  She told us we could try to get some people to move at the bar to make room for 2 people, but we could not sit at this other bar area where there were chairs and no one in them.  I requested a table and she said since we weren't eating we could not sit at a table.  Reasonable rule at 7pm - at 10:30pm when there are open tables and no one waiting....sounded like she preferred we didn't stay.  So we didn't.  And I won't be back.  Don't go to this place.
we go every year we're in town the best!

I like the beers- some bartenders are better than others. One of those places where they try to squeeze too many people into a small bar. As a vegetarian, the smell of buttery mussels can be a bit overpowering at times. Bathrooms are tidy (and individual) which is nice

This was the third Belgian restaurant in DC that I have tried. I brought a friend of mine from Pittsburgh (who has an authentic waffle place 3 blocks from her house) and we came here for dessert because they listed Liege Waffles on the menu. Having lived in Brussels for a couple years, I've been on the look-out for a local place to get a good Belgian waffle (The other two places don't have them on the menu).  Well, folks, I hate to say it but these waffles are plain American waffles. Definitely not Liege waffles. Definitely not worth $9.  Still on the search for a Liege waffle someplace closer than Pittsburgh.  I will consider coming back to try the rest of the menu and write a new review. But I won't be having dessert.
A nice selection of Belgium beers and mussels. What else could you ask for?

I went here on Saturday night and the vibe and food was great.  They have a good selection of beers on tap and the mussels are some of the best in town. I recommend the Mussels St Arnold.  Ask for extra bread you’re going to need it to soak up all the good sauce once you eat the mussels.  Good times.

If you are able to get here for happy hour (3:30-6:30), you can enjoy a great priced bowl of mussels on the cheap (11 bucks) ~otherwise its 19.  St. Arnolds features a flat priced structure with lots of options.  I personally enjoyed the creamy st arnolds house special -- the old bay infused eastern shore was a bit too salty for me.  Their fries (which come with every mussel platter) are pretty fantastic.  Most importantly, their beer selection is solid -- featuring lots of monastary brews.  Service was quick and appreciative -- although I went after happy hour, so I may need to adjust this once I return. No outdoor area (at least that I found which was a let down...)  Regardless I recommend giving one of the St. Arnolds branches a shot!
Great food!! Friendly people and an amazing Flemish onion soup.

Great place for mussels and frites!  They come in super-hot cast iron crocks, bubbling at the table. I hear all of the mussel choices are good, but I can't get past the "mussels st arnolds".  The broth has Belgian beer and duck fat... Enough said.  This place is down a half level... a sort of hole in the wall place with great atmosphere.  Its pretty small though, so if you can get a reservation, do so.

I don't write reviews.....EVER....But had a burget here yesterday on CT Ave NW... And MANNNN!!! The loaded buger on the brunch menu is the best burger i've had in years...Just fantastic and the fries were awesome too...

Loved the Thai curry mussels.  The people I was with weren't particularly impressed by the waffles since they were just regular waffles, the batter needed to be lighter to be a Belgian waffle.  Good beer selection.
Fantastic! House Mussels, drinks, staff all outstanding!

Great beer but my wife and I went there and the bar was full.  We sat at a table (and there were plenty of open tables) and we were continuously told that we "should be ordering food" if we were sitting at a table.  Needless to say we left.  It would be one thing if they were packed but if there are plenty of open tables it shouldn't be a big deal. They were flat out rude.
Love this place more than any other in DC. Always great!

Very good non-pretentious neighborhood bar/restaurant serving very good quality mussels in a variety of styles, along with your normal assortment of wings,  burgers and sandwiches (for dessert try the waffles, nutella is an option). They also have a very nice beer selection too for a local bar (including some nice Belgians) in draft or bottle format.  Very friendly staff.  Crowds here seem to be pretty relaxed and non-hipstery lol. All in all, a quintessential neighborhood bar.

If you go here early in the evening, it's not that crowded at all -- in fact, it's a great place to hold a conversation while nursing a quality belgian beer and inhaling the aroma of delicious mussels. But their other dishes are great too -- for example, try the onion rings. Yum. The staff is incredibly warm and welcoming. One of my favorite places.
GREAT mussels and beer menu. VERY LOUD. It was a Friday nite, but will definitely be going back.
Their mussels are delish!  Or if you're too scared, you can settle with a chicken sandwich like my bf, lulz.
The best muscles, fries, and burgers! A great local spot with a new regular.
